What is Schema Manager?

It's a plugin for GetSimple CMS 3.1 that allow you to save information in a DB type manner 
but data is saved in XML files.

So the Schema is basically a table with various fields to hold you information. 

As of now we support the following field types:

o - text, normal text box
o - textlong, full width Text Box
o - Checkbox, Checkbox.
o - pages, a dropdown of the current Pages. 
o - templates, a dropdown of the current templates
o - datepicker, a date picker field. 
o - datetimepicker, a date and time picker. 
o - image, an image selector field
o - textarea, a plain textarea
o - codeeditor, a codemirror textarea
o - texteditor, a CKEditor enabled textarea. 

So you setup your Schemas, add some fields and input data into those fields. 

The front end allows you to run SQL type queries on the data to build your webpages. 

So what can you use it for ?

Anything !!

How about a Blog, set up your schema "blog" 
add some fields, "title, author, publisheddate, content" 
Enter your data. 


On the front end its as simple as running, 
$r = array();
$r = $sql->query("SELECT id,title,author,publisheddate,content FROM blog ORDER BY publisheddate DESC");





